<title>UK: Burford buys site for 9.4 mln stg from RTZ.</title>
<headline>Burford buys site for 9.4 mln stg from RTZ.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1996-12-16</dateline>
<text>
<p>Property company Burford Holdings Plc said on Monday that it is buying a 452 acre site in Avonmouth in south western England from RTZ Estates Ltd, a subsidiary of RTZ Corp Plc, for 9.4 million stg in cash.</p>
<p>It said that planning consent already exists on 185 acres of the site for industrial and distribution buildings.</p>
<p>&quot;We are extremely excited by the prospect of creating the south-west's premier distribution centre,&quot; John Anderson, a director of Burford said in a statement.</p>
<p>-- London Newsroom +44 171 542 4019</p>
